UI <-----> model <-----> layers

AnimatedLayer
    |- SimpleAnimatedLayer
    |   |- InterpolatedAnimatedLayer
    |   |   |- ... 
    |   |   |- ... (much children with interpolation methods)
    |   |   |- ... 
    |   |       |- NormalAnimatedLayer
    |
    |- ControlAnimatedLayer
    |   |- LoopAnimatedLayer
    |   |- Interpolating control layer?..

AnimatedLayer:
* - to be defined in animatedLayer
# - pure virtual in animatedLayer
Others can be redefined in children
% - protected

    getUpdatedFrame(int num)         *  |
    getCachedFrame(int num)          #  | For any frame
    updateFrame(int num)            %   |
    
    getKeyFrame(int num)             #  |
    getNextKeyFrame(int num)         *  | For key frames
    getPreviousKeyFrame(int num)     *  |

    isKeyFrame(int num)                 | bool
    getNextKey(int num)              #  | Returning numbers
    getPreviousKey(int num)          #  |
    
    loadFrames()

SimpleAnimatedLayer:
    getCachedFrame(int num)             |
    
    getKeyFrame(int num)             *  |
    getNextKey(int num)              *  |
    getPreviousKey(int num)          *  |

InterpolatedAnimatedLayer:
    getCachedFrame(int num)          *  | 
    updateFrame(int num)             *  |
    
    interpolate(from, to, position)  #  |


FrameLayer:
    isKeyFrame()
    
